Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.09,0:01:41.15,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Soseki Kite Battle Over London!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.95,0:02:00.97,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the famous Rosetta Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:03.48,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes it is, Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.70,0:02:04.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:09.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This description is written\Nin ancient Egyptian.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:11.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This description is\Nwritten in Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.04,0:02:13.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The contents of both\Ndescriptions are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.81,0:02:15.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The French scholar, Champollion,\Nwas the one who deciphered...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:18.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the ancient Egyptian language.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:23.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This stone is a treasure of England.\NNow we can read the Mummy's language.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:24.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,May I say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.89,0:02:29.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The people who discovered this\Nstone in Rosetta, Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.39,0:02:31.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,were soldiers in the army of\NNapoleon The First.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:33.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who found\Nthe Rosetta Stone was also French.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.83,0:02:36.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And the person who deciphered the\Nancient Egyptian language was French!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.27,0:02:39.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of this, why is\Nthis stone in England?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.40,0:02:41.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.57,0:02:45.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This stone should\Nbelong to us in France!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.58,0:02:47.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,May I say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:49.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The land of Rosetta is in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:52.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So Egypt has the right\Nto keep the Rosetta Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.75,0:02:54.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,One third of the language they\Nwrote on the stone is in Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.99,0:02:58.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I, as a Greek, insist on having\None third ownership of the stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:03:00.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,May I say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.13,0:03:00.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.36,0:03:03.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:04.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:06.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say you're Egyptian!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.60,0:03:08.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.87,0:03:09.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? Get lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.93,0:03:10.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:13.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I am who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:14.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.57,0:03:16.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:47.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the mummy talk.\NI feel something bad might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.37,0:03:49.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hoping that a group of\Ndistinguished professors, like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.17,0:03:50.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,could give this a thorough\Nscientific analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:53.18,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,- I wonder if he's speaking the truth or not.\N- It must be some mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.18,0:03:55.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:03:59.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This room has been kept\Nclosed since the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.63,0:04:09.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.43,0:04:10.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:10.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.96,0:04:11.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:31.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait! Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.05,0:04:34.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.26,0:04:41.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.23,0:04:44.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.16,0:04:45.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.23,0:04:46.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.87,0:04:47.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,On your right!\NYour right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:48.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:54.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.91,0:04:57.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.41,0:04:58.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.08,0:05:01.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How could a stone\Nfly off into the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.18,0:05:03.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's against the great laws\Nof Sir Isaac Newton!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:05.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I must be dreaming now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:06.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! This is just a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.42,0:05:12.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! This is a dream.\NSo long Mr. Rosetta Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:16.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Good bye! My honey, Rosettina!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:21.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Good bye! Good bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.87,0:05:27.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you guys sticking\Nyour noses in my dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.04,0:05:31.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NIs this really a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:33.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! This is not a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:36.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my god!\NWhat am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We did a great job.\NHurry up and get to Dover!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:06:01.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the mummy's ghost did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.77,0:06:05.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The mummy got angry because\Npeople discovered the secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:08.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,of their language after\Nthe Rosetta Stone was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:11.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He was unhappy because they woke\Nhim up from his eternal sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.15,0:06:13.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well Chief,\Ndon't rush to conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:18.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody who really wanted the\NRosetta Stone must have done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:21.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, the Rosetta Stone\Nis a treasure of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.29,0:06:23.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There are always people who\Nare trying to steal treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.80,0:06:26.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If nobody was interested in stealing\Nit, then it's not even a treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:31.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,However, about the\Nmummy doing this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.51,0:06:45.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, who stole the stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:48.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,French, Egyptian, Greek...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.99,0:06:58.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,anybody who has some connection\Nto the stone, wants to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:02.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That stone is a treasure that\Nhas brought ancient Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.37,0:07:03.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,into the modern world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:07.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But they stole it from the sky.\NIt's a cunning strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.31,0:07:09.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think they used a blimp?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:12.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, yesterday's wind velocity\Nwas more than 60 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.54,0:07:15.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they used an air plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.55,0:07:18.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think they\Ncould have used an air plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.55,0:07:21.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody seems to have heard\Nthe sound of an air plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.29,0:07:24.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Watson, why don't we\Ngo out and eat French food tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.02,0:07:27.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,since we haven't done\Nthat for a long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.89,0:07:29.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What? French food?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.09,0:07:33.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mrs. Hudson,\Nwould you like to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:35.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:46.00,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,- Allons enfants de la patrie...\N- Arise children of the fatherland...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:49.84,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lejour de gloire est arrivé!\N- The day of glory has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.48,0:07:54.65,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,- Contre nous, de la tyrannie...\N- Against us tyranny's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.05,0:07:59.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'étendard sanglant est levé.\N- Bloody standard is raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:03.52,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,- Entendez vous dans les campagnes...\N- Listen to the sound in the fields...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:05.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Napoleon...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.46,0:08:07.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,you look like you're\Nhaving a fun time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.90,0:08:11.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop laughing after I heard\Nthat the Rosetta Stone disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:13.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,from the British Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.01,0:08:18.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Napoleon found that stone and\NChampollion deciphered the letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:21.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,sculpted on the stone first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:23.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, France should\Nkeep that stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:27.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean someone\NFrench stole that stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.29,0:08:29.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.95,0:08:32.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The French people are\Nnever thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:45.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need change!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.60,0:08:47.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:50.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, why did he rush\Nto leave so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:54.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That man must have hired\Nsomebody to steal the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.15,0:09:00.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he didn't use a blimp or an\Nair plane, he must be very smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:04.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I already have some idea\Nhow they did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.72,0:09:07.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's enjoy our dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:08.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:10.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:15.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.43,0:09:18.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, his name is\NKinnosuke Natsume.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:21.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a young professor who came here\Nto study the culture of England...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:23.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,from the far eastern\Ncountry of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.84,0:09:27.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how is he related\Nto this incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.28,0:09:31.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There are big typhoons that strike\NJapan over and over...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:33.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,from summer to autumn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:34.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:39.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,European people try to control nature,\Nbut Japanese people know how to use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:42.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and adapt to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.60,0:09:53.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,K. Natsume...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:02.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very interested about\Nthe incident of the Rosetta Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.78,0:10:05.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?\NHas something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:09.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, about one month ago...\NWhen I was returning home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.73,0:10:15.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.99,0:10:16.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.33,0:10:23.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.17,0:10:28.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.38,0:10:36.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:02.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the other students were\Nmaking joke, at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:05.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the attitude of those two\Npeople was very suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.28,0:11:15.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They stole an illustration book that\NI brought from Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:17.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,that was translated into English.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And the book had a story\Nabout a thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.46,0:11:22.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,who used the big wind\Nto steal things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.63,0:11:24.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Used the big wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:27.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's a big castle\Nin Nagoya, Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:31.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A monster fish with the head of\Na tiger and the body of a fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:34.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,called Shachihoko is on the top of\Nthe castle, to protect it from fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:38.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The scales of the monster fish\Nare made of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.04,0:11:41.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A hundred years ago,\Non the night of a storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:44.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a thief who stole\Nthe scales of the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.35,0:11:45.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.88,0:11:47.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you understand, Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:50.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a smart detective,\NMr. Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.06,0:11:53.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:57.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was wondering about\Nthe book they had stolen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:11:59.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the Rosetta Stone\Nincident happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.30,0:12:02.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thank you very much\NMr. Kinnosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.23,0:12:03.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there's a person\Nwho ordered those men...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:05.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,to steal your picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.17,0:12:08.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He got the idea from the book\Nand committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.17,0:12:11.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you don't have to\Nworry any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:13.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We will take care of this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.88,0:12:15.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:17.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:18.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:21.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.19,0:12:29.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If they stole the Rosetta Stone,\Nwhere did they hide it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:32.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some idea where.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.34,0:12:43.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no Rosetta Stone?!\NI wanted to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.07,0:12:44.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just like a party\Nwith no cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:47.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is Scotland Yard doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.48,0:12:56.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rosetta Stone might be hidden\Nsomewhere between London and Dover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.99,0:13:00.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mr. Holmes, do you already\Nknow the place where they hid it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:02.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:05.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go over there and\Ntake it back with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:12.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm already tired today. I'll make\Nsure I bring the stone back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:14.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,B... but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:16.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:20.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'll never\Nlet the stone get to Dover.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.41,0:13:22.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you Holmes!\NI'll never let you do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.95,0:13:24.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are trying to stop\Nme tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:27.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Professor Moriarty, will\Ntake action tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:43.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Your tea will get cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.27,0:13:52.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Holmes, do you really\Nknow where they hid the Rosetta Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.14,0:13:55.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, to tell the truth,\NI don't have any idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.88,0:13:57.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.42,0:14:01.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who knows\Nis Moriarty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:03.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:06.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, I hope a strong wind\Nwill blow again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.11,0:14:32.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's mine is mine\Nand what's yours is also mine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.65,0:14:40.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's mine is mine\Nand what's yours is also mine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:46.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Long live France!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:48.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Long live France!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:58.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a problem.\NHolmes found out about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.31,0:15:03.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that true? He might have\Nfound out at the restaurant!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.48,0:15:05.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.02,0:15:08.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He is bragging that he will\Nfind it tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.85,0:15:11.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm sure he doesn't know\Nthe Rosetta Stone is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.89,0:15:13.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, why didn't you tell me that first?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:17.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's cross the ocean,\Nand move this to France, tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:24.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't play with it!\NOh, excuse me! Wait! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.04,0:15:31.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.75,0:15:37.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.55,0:15:42.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.83,0:15:54.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go! Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.73,0:15:58.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd! Smiley!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:00.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.70,0:16:02.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare the kite!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:03.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.48,0:16:06.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:23.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Run fast as soon as\Nthe wind starts to blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.46,0:16:26.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:53.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave ho! Heave ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.79,0:16:59.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it amazing that you can cross\Nover the Straits of Dover so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can already see the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.94,0:17:07.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Mr. Rich descendent of Napoleon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.24,0:17:09.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you pay me the amount\Nyou promised me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:14.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, congratulations for the\Ngood job. Let's shake hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.75,0:17:17.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! I don't want to shake hands!\NWhy don't you give me 10,000 pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.62,0:17:20.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Non! Non! I don't want\Nto pay even 1 pound...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.55,0:17:22.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,until we arrive safely in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.49,0:17:24.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stingy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:29.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not stingy. We French make a\Ndistinction between right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.29,0:17:32.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Make the rope longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.14,0:17:45.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.32,0:17:55.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty, good evening\Nfrom the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:17:57.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Rats!\NHow could this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.16,0:18:02.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd, Smiley!\NUse battle plan #302!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.13,0:18:05.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Start the battle!\NStart the battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.66,0:18:09.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger! Battle plan #302...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.83,0:18:10.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,start!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:33.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinnosuke, how are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.72,0:18:35.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing all right!\NLeave this up to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:36.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,In Japan, we have a game called\N"kite battle".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.33,0:18:38.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We cut our opponent's rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.30,0:18:42.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.37,0:18:43.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.71,0:18:53.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.38,0:18:54.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Operation number 105!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.05,0:18:56.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.78,0:18:57.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:04.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll make it this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:07.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.69,0:19:08.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The engine is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:10.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:11.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:12.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.57,0:19:20.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.40,0:19:23.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,L... let me go!\NProtect your own life by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.28,0:19:28.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.15,0:19:29.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:32.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Protect your own life by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:34.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't say such mean things!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.19,0:19:45.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinnosuke! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.86,0:19:46.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.66,0:19:48.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.44,0:19:57.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes might have given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.17,0:19:58.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's coming over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.28,0:20:03.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!\NIt will crush us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:09.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:13.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd! Smiley!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.59,0:20:14.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring down the kite quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:16.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:22.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something was fishy\Nso I came here to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.00,0:20:24.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I found you guys here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:25.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.57,0:20:31.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so close!\NThe kite will fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.35,0:20:42.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.02,0:20:45.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:49.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.70,0:20:57.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, bring it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.04,0:20:58.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:01.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.94,0:21:07.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!\NHeave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.92,0:21:14.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is it!\NI'm going to swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:17.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Spinning! Spinning! Spinning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.56,0:21:29.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do that!\NWe have a ship down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:33.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.52,0:21:52.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:53.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We won!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.75,0:22:18.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to have things\Nback in their proper place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.42,0:22:19.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.28,0:22:23.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rosetta Stone is a symbol of\Nthe British Museum.
